---
title: "BuzzLLM — Chat Flow Sequence (L3)"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant main as main.rs
    participant prompts as prompts mod
    participant registry as ToolRegistry
    participant llm as invoke_llm
    participant provider as Provider
    participant output as print_to_stdout
    participant api as LLM API

    User->>main: CLI args (model, url, prompt, provider, ...)
    main->>prompts: get_prompt(system_prompt)
    prompts-->>main: resolved prompt text

    main->>registry: register tools based on --system-prompt name
    registry-->>main: tool schemas (OpenAI or Anthropic format)

    main->>main: construct LlmOptions
    main->>llm: invoke_llm(opts, prompt, system_prompt, provider, registry, sse, brief)

    loop for each iteration (max_infer_iters)
        llm->>provider: build_request(opts, prompt, system_prompt)
        provider-->>llm: RequestArgs (data + headers)

        llm->>api: POST streaming request (reqwest, timeout=900s)
        api-->>llm: SSE byte stream

        loop for each SSE line
            llm->>provider: parse_sse_line(line, message_started, tool_calls, current_id)
            provider-->>llm: Vec of StreamResponse
            llm->>output: print_to_stdout(response, sse, brief)
            output-->>User: colored text or SSE events
        end

        alt no tool_calls
            Note over llm: break — done
        else has tool_calls
            llm->>registry: execute each tool concurrently
            registry-->>llm: tool results
            llm->>output: print tool results
            llm->>provider: assemble_tool_messages(messages, tool_calls)
            Note over llm: clear tool_calls, loop
        end
    end

    llm->>registry: cleanup (kills pythonexec container if running)
    llm->>output: print ResponseEnd
    output-->>User: === [ DONE ] ===
